commitResults.messageBody: Not currently functional. Seeking sanity check.

With this PR, the format of the storage file has been changed. If you run the app with the same storage file, it will be unable to load. To remedy this, either:

1. Go into your `data/addressbook.json`, and the "groups" in the corresponding spot: 
```
"persons" : [
// persons
],
"groups" : [ ]
```
2. Work from an empty address book and add people from there. The data will be correctly saved from now on.

commitResults.messageBody:
FilteredList does not have sorting functionality.

Let's
* Wrap the existing FilteredList with a SortedList to
enable sorting capabilities.
* Rename getFilteredPersonList() to getPersonList() to reflect that
the list may be both filtered and sorted.
* Update getPersonList() to return the SortedList, which observes
changes in the FilteredList and updates accordingly.
* Implement methods to update the sort comparator, allowing the
list to be sorted based on different criteria.

Future calls to the list command after sorting will present
the sorted list until the sort parameter is cleared.
